        <h2 class="cag-h2">What Is It Like to Live With a Congo African Grey Every Day?</h2>
        <p>Living with a Congo African Grey is like sharing your home with a clever, opinionated toddler who never grows up — richly rewarding, and genuinely demanding. Ours are raised to slot into family life, but a Congo needs daily interaction, mental work, and a fresh, varied diet to stay happy over its 40–60 year lifetime.</p>
        <img class="sec-img inf-img" src={IMG + "living-with-a-congo-african-grey-family-lifestyle.webp"} srcset={IMG + "living-with-a-congo-african-grey-family-lifestyle-760.webp 760w, " + IMG + "living-with-a-congo-african-grey-family-lifestyle.webp 1408w"} sizes="(max-width:860px) 92vw, 760px" width="1408" height="768" loading="lazy" decoding="async" alt="A Congo African Grey as part of daily family life on a play stand in a warm, sunlit living room" />

        <h3 class="cag-h3">How Much Time and Enrichment Does a Congo Need?</h3>
        <p>Plan on several hours of out-of-cage time and active engagement a day, plus rotating foraging toys and puzzles to keep that big brain busy. A well-fed, well-stimulated Congo is a sweet companion; a bored or poorly-fed one develops the screaming and feather-plucking that lands birds in rescues.</p>
        <img class="sec-img og-photo" src={IMG + "congo-african-grey-fresh-chop-diet.webp"} srcset={IMG + "congo-african-grey-fresh-chop-diet-760.webp 760w, " + IMG + "congo-african-grey-fresh-chop-diet.webp 1408w"} sizes="(max-width:860px) 92vw, 760px" width="1408" height="768" loading="lazy" decoding="async" alt="A bowl of fresh chop and pellets, the varied daily diet a Congo African Grey needs" />

        <h4 class="cag-h4">Diet, Calcium and a Congo's Long-Term Health</h4>
        <p>A healthy Congo eats a base of quality pellets plus daily fresh chop, with calcium sources like cuttlebone to support bone and feather health over the decades. Getting nutrition right early is the cheapest health insurance there is for a bird that will outlive most family pets many times over.</p>
        <img class="sec-img og-photo" src={IMG + "congo-african-grey-calcium-cuttlebone-supplement.webp"} srcset={IMG + "congo-african-grey-calcium-cuttlebone-supplement-760.webp 760w, " + IMG + "congo-african-grey-calcium-cuttlebone-supplement.webp 1408w"} sizes="(max-width:860px) 92vw, 760px" width="1408" height="768" loading="lazy" decoding="async" alt="Cuttlebone and calcium supplements provided to support a Congo African Grey's long-term health" />

        <h3 class="cag-h3">Watch Our Congo African Greys Talk and Play</h3>
        <p>Because photos can be stolen but honest video is hard to fake, here's one of our own Congos at home — no narration, no stock footage. Short of driving to Midland yourself, it's the most direct proof we can hand you that these birds are real.</p>
